<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bedlam (AMC Sunday at 1:30 p.m., again at 8 p.m.): Directed by Mark Robson, 
this Val Lewton-produced chiller stars Boris Karloff as the head of the 
notorious London madhouse. (1:30) 
</P>
<P>
Breezy (Channel 13 Tuesday at 3:30 a.m.): Clint Eastwood's memorable, 
heart-tugging May-December romance with Kay Lenz and William Holden. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
The Old-Fashioned Way (Channel 5 Thursday at 4 a.m.): W. C. Fields finds 
himself managing a traveling company performing "The Drunkard." This is the one 
in which Fields meets his match in Baby Leroy. (1:30) 
</P>
<P>
The Band Wagon (Channel 5 Friday at 1:30 a.m.): Classic Vincente 
Minnelli-directed backstage musical with Fred Astaire, Cyd Charisse, Oscar 
Levant, Nanette Fabray and Jack Buchanan. (2:00) 
</P>
</TEXT>
