<HEADLINE>
<P>
ART OF ART CRITICISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding William Wilson's June 18 article about "The Dada and Surrealist 
Word-Image" show at LACMA: Could Calendar please hire an art critic who will 
discuss things such as composition, medium and context instead of the car in 
front of him as he was leaving the museum? 
</P>
<P>
Wilson's condescending, self-absorbed efforts to prove he is just as clever and 
hip as the artist he writes around are tiresome. 
</P>
<P>
He is guilty of what he so often criticizes in exhibit catalogues: Artspeak and 
obfuscation: "In the big picture, the dilemma of the modern artist has been 
that history lopped off his traditional function." Say what? 
</P>
<P>
JOEL WALLERIUS 
</P>
<P>
Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
