<HEADLINE>
<P>
MINIMALISM DEBATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Concerning Donna Perlmutter's "The Growing Debate Over Minimalism," June 18: 
</P>
<P>
The eminent British composer Benjamin Britten, who was not an academician and 
certainly not a minimalist, was asked during an interview about the various 
compositional styles of the 20th Century. He replied that "the important thing 
is not what style a person composes in but whether the chap has anything to 
say." 
</P>
<P>
It seems that about all the academicians and minimalists have to say are 
commentaries they give about their music. 
</P>
<P>
KENNETH LEAVENS 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 
</P>
</TEXT>
