<P>
TEST RESULTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Because of John Matuszak's prominence, tests were done as quickly as possible 
(June 19). Hmm . . . it's a shame he wasn't a little less prominent, so as to 
get lost in the shuffle as my girlfriend did. (It took nine weeks for the 
results.) 
</P>
<P>
To Lilia Shelton, coroner's supervising investigator: How about dealing from 
the top of the deck? 
</P>
<P>
TOM NOVIKOFF 
</P>
<P>
Santa Fe Springs 
</P>
