<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE RUB IS THERE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In his essay on Marshall McLuhan, Thomas Cahill states that "virtually 
everybody admits to not having finished any of his books. . . ." I certainly 
believe that Cahill is included. To refer to his most famous work, "The Medium 
is the Massage," as "The Medium is the Message" is to say very little regarding 
Cahill's undertaking of the work. Aye, there's the rub! 
</P>
<P>
S. R. GROSSLIGHT 
</P>
<P>
MANHATTAN BEACH 
</P>
