<HEADLINE>
<P>
EL CAJON MAN HELD IN BUSINESS THEFTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 29-year-old El Cajon man, who has been linked by authorities to recent 
business burglaries, was arrested early Saturday morning, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Anthony Wayne Smith was arrested on suspicion of six counts of burglary and 
taken to County Jail, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Police responding to an alarm at a hobby shop in the 400 block of Broadway 
shortly after 5 a.m. Saturday saw Smith -- with an armload of merchandise -- 
standing in a parking lot behind the store. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities searched Smith's home and reported finding items linked to 
commercial businesses that had also been burglarized within the past three 
weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
