<HEADLINE>
<P>
INDULGING THE PASTA PASSION; 
</P>
<P>
AN ITCH FOR ITALIAN? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins DR, TED ENGELBART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bellini's Trattoria, 12021 West Pico Blvd., West L.A. (213) 477-4057. Style: 
Neighborhood trattoria with menu full of bright spots. Setting: Bleak. 
Recommended dishes: Eggplant and goat cheese calzone; bow-tie pasta with 
artichoke hearts and walnuts; saffron linguine with fresh tomato coulis. Cost 
per person, food only: $15-$30. 
</P>
<P>
Fresco, 514 S. Brand Blvd., Glendale. (818) 247-5541. Style: Serious contender 
for best Valley restaurant. Setting: Courtyard with skylight and fake ivy. 
Recommended dishes: Corn crepe stuffed with duck; insalata tricolore; risotto 
with lamb. Cost per person, food only: $25-$40. 
</P>
<P>
Louise's Trattoria, 232 N. Larchmont Blvd., Los Angeles. (213) 962-9510. Style: 
Italian chain serving large portions at affordable prices. Setting: Pink 
coffeeshopesque. Recommended dishes: Chopped salad; tagliatelle with sausage 
and ground beef; capellini with shrimp and dill cream. Cost per person, food 
only: $12-$25. 
</P>
<P>
Orso, 8706 W. Third St., Los Angeles. (213) 274-7144. Style: Trendy trattoria 
for plebs and celebs. Setting: Cosmopolitan -- with one of the nicest patios in 
town. Recommended dishes: Arugula, endive and tomato salad with Parmesan; 
tagliatelle with grilled vegetables; veal scaloppine. Cost per person, food 
only: $20-$40. 
</P>
<P>
Tuttopasta, 417 S. Hill St., Los Angeles. (213) 621-2625. Style: Stepchild of 
trendy Tuttobene. Setting: Pure plastic set in the old Subway Terminal 
building. Recommended dishes: Pasta e fagioli; penne all'arrabbiata; roast 
chicken sandwich; Cost per person, food only: $8-$15. Kathie JenkinsDR, TED 
ENGELBART 
</P>
</TEXT>
